Parallel Hamiltonian Solver

Two modes: CSV mode (takes parameters from file of J,Bx,Bz)
Usage: ./matgen <num_qbits> range <j> <num_bx> <init_bx> <stop_bx> <num_bz> <init_bz> <stop_bz>
Usage: ./matgen <num_qbits> csv <filename>

Optional Arguments:
--save-components-ascii        : saves J, Bx, Bz as human-readable files.
--save-components-petsc        : saves J, Bx, Bz as PETSC-readable files.
--print-eigenvalue-information : Prints additional info for each eigenvalue.
--run-performance-metrics     : show performance metrics after solve.
--perform-eigenvalue-check    : ensure the matrix was diagonalized correctly by checking that mat * eigvec = lambda * eigvec.
--verbose                     : print information during matrix generation.
--file=<filestr>              : saves eigenset output to a different file.